<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1771,2014]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1437,151,969]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,482,1915,1942]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Description. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[351,475,1915,1942]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Both sexes</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Head rounded trapezoidal (
<figureCitation box="[792,874,1915,1941]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–14" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[171,1410,197,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[167,1420,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 10–14. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) saburrata new species ex Coracina lineata ombriosa. 10, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 11, male genitalia, dorsal view. 12, male mesosome, ventral view. 13, male paramere, dorsal view. 14, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825555" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825555/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
), lateral margins of preantennal head slightly convex, frons slightly concave. Marginal carina broad, narrowing gradually anteriorly, deeply displaced and widened at osculum.Ventral anterior plate small, crescent-shaped. Head chaetotaxy as in 
<figureCitation box="[998,1078,1987,2013]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–14" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[171,1410,197,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[167,1420,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 10–14. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) saburrata new species ex Coracina lineata ombriosa. 10, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 11, male genitalia, dorsal view. 12, male mesosome, ventral view. 13, male paramere, dorsal view. 14, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825555" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825555/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
. Preantennal nodi large, bulging. Pre- and post-ocular nodi large, connected dorsally by broad ocular band. Marginal temporal carina slender. Gular plate triangular. Thoracic and abdominal segments as in 
<figureCitation box="[774,873,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–9" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1941,1965]" captionTargetBox="[170,1416,197,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-23@6.[151,1436,181,1917]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 8–9. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) saburrata new species ex Coracina lineata ombriosa. 8, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 9, female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825553" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825553/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Figs 8–9</figureCitation>
. Base pigmentation translucent; preocular and preantennal nodi dark brown; mandibular framework, margins of antennal sockets, ocular band, postocular nodi, gular plate, proepimera, metepisterna, sternal plates IV–VI and subgenital plates medium brown; meso- and metasternal plates and sternal plates II–III pale brown.
</paragraph>
